{"title_page": "Lajpat Nagar metro station", "text_new": "{{short description|metro station in Delhi, India}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=July 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2015}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name            = [[File:Delhi Metro logo.svg|50px]]<br />Lajpat Nagar\n| type            = '''[[Delhi Metro]]''' '''[[List of Delhi metro stations|station]]'''\n| style           = Delhi Metro\n| image           = Lajpat Nagar Metro Station Platform.jpg\n| image_caption   = Lajpat Nagar Metro Station Platform\n| address         = Lala Lajpat Rai Marg, New Delhi 110024, India\n| coordinates     = {{coord|28.570607|77.236474}}\n| line            = {{color box|#{{Delhi Metro color|Violet}}}} [[Violet Line (Delhi Metro)|Violet Line]]\n{{color box|#{{Delhi Metro color|Pink}}}} [[Pink Line (Delhi Metro)|Pink Line]]\n| other           = \n| structure       = [[Elevated]], Underground\n| platform        = [[Side platform]]<br />Platform-1 \u2192 [[Escorts Mujesar metro station|Escorts Mujesar]]<br />Platform-2 \u2192[[Kashmere Gate metro station|Kashmere Gate]] via [[Lal Qila metro station|Lal Qila]]<br />Platform-3 \u2192 [[Shiv Vihar metro station|Shiv Vihar]] <br />Platform-4 \u2192 [[Majlis Park metro station|Majlis Park]]\n| depth           = \n| levels          = 2\n| tracks          = 4\n| parking         = {{parking symbol}} Available\n| bicycle         = \n| opened          = Violet Line- {{start date and age|2010|October|3|mf=yes}} <br />\nPink Line- {{start date and age|2018|08|6|mf=yes}} <br />\n| closed          = \n| rebuilt         = \n| electrified     = 25 kV 50 Hz AC through [[overhead catenary]]\n| ADA             = Yes {{access icon}}\n| code            = LJPN\n| owned           = [[Delhi Metro]]\n| operator        = [[Delhi Metro Rail Corporation]] (DMRC)\n| zone            = \n| smartcardname   = \n| smartcardstatus = \n| former          = \n| passengers      = \n| pass_year       = \n| pass_rank       = \n| pass_percent    = \n| pass_system     = \n| mpassengers     = \n| services        = {{S-rail|title=Delhi Metro}}\n{{S-line|system=Delhi Metro|line=Violet |previous= Jangpura |next= Moolchand}}\n{{S-line|system=Delhi Metro|line=Pink |previous= South Extension |next= Vinobapuri}}\n| map_locator     = {{Location map|India Delhi| lat=28.570607|long=77.236474| width=300|caption= Location in Delhi|label='''Lajpat Nagar''' metro station}}\n}}\n\n'''Lajpat Nagar''' is an interchange station between [[Violet Line (Delhi Metro)|Violet Line]] and [[Pink Line (Delhi Metro)|Pink Line]] of the [[Delhi Metro]] in [[Delhi]]. It is located between [[Jangpura (Delhi Metro)|Jangpura]] and [[Moolchand (Delhi Metro)|Moolchand]] on the [[Violet Line (Delhi Metro)|Violet Line]] in [[Lajpat Nagar]]. The station was opened with the first section of the Violet Line on 3 October 2010, in time for the Commonwealth Games opening ceremony on the same day.<ref>{{cite press release| url=http://www.delhimetrorail.com/press_reldetails.aspx?id=OZixKt2MNIslld| title=Central Secretariat \u2013 Sarita Vihar Corridor Opens for Commuter Operations Tomorrow| publisher=Delhi Metro}}</ref>\nIt became an interchange station with the opening of the Pink Line on 6 August 2018. The station on the Pink Line is underground, whereas the Violet line station is elevated. However, both the lines are seamlessly connected, without the commuters having to exit the ticketed area to interchange from one line to another.\n\n[[Lajpat Nagar Market]] is one of the famous shopping market in Delhi which is famous for women clothes, artificial jewelry, Footwear and Home Decor items. This market is just 200-300 meter away from Lajpat Nagar Metro Station. Timings of this market is 11:00 AM to 08:00 PM\n\n==The station==\n===Station layout=== \nElevated Violet Line\n{|table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=3\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;border-top:solid 1px gray;\" width=50 valign=top|'''G'''\n|style=\"border-top:solid 1px gray;border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=100 valign=top|Street Level\n|style=\"border-top:solid 1px gray;border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=500 valign=top|Exit/Entrance\n|-\n|valign=top|'''L1'''\n|valign=top|Mezzanine\n|valign=top|Fare control, station agent, Metro Card vending machines, crossover<br/>\n|-\n|style=\"border-top:solid 1px gray;border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=50 rowspan=4 valign=top|'''L2'''\n|style=\"border-top:solid 1px gray;border-right:solid 2px black;border-left:solid 2px black;border-bottom:solid 2px black;text-align:center;\" colspan=2|<small>[[Side platform]] No- 1, doors will open on the left {{access icon}}</small>\n|-\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=100|<span style=color:#{{Delhi Metro color|Violet}}>'''Southbound'''</span>\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=500|<small>Towards \u2192[[Escorts Mujesar metro station|Escorts Mujesar]]</small> \n|-\n|<span style=color:#{{Delhi Metro color|Violet}}>'''Northbound'''</span> \n|<span style=color:white>\u2192</span><small>Towards \u2190[[Kashmere Gate metro station|Kashmere Gate]]</small>\n|-\n|style=\"border-top:solid 2px black;border-right:solid 2px black;border-left:solid 2px black;border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" colspan=2  align=center|<small>[[Side platform]] No- 2, doors will open on the left {{access icon}}</small>\n|-\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=50 rowspan=2 valign=top|'''L2'''\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=100|\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=500|\n|-\n|}\n\n===Station layout=== \nUnderground Pink Line\n{|table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=3\n|style=\"border-top:solid 1px gray;border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=50 valign=top|'''G'''\n|style=\"border-top:solid 1px gray;border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=100 valign=top|Street Level\n|style=\"border-top:solid 1px gray;border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=390 valign=top|Exit/ Entrance\n|-\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\"|'''M'''\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\"|Mezzanine\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\"|Fare control, station agent, Ticket/token, shops\n|-\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=50 rowspan=3 valign=top|'''P'''\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px white;\" width=100|<span style=color:#{{Delhi Metro color|Pink}}>'''Southbound'''</span>\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px white;\" width=390|Platform 3 \u2192 [[Shiv Vihar metro station|Shiv Vihar]] \n|-\n|style=\"border-top:solid 2px black;border-right:solid 2px black;border-left:solid 2px black;border-bottom:solid 2px black;text-align:center;\" colspan=2|<small>[[Island platform]], doors will open on the right</small> {{access icon}}\n|-\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=100|<span style=color:#{{Delhi Metro color|Pink}}>'''Northbound'''</span>\n| style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=\"390\" |Platform 4 Toward \u2190 [[Majlis Park metro station|Majlis Park]]  \n|}\n\n===Facilities===\nList of available ATM at Lajpat Nagar metro station are HDFC Bank, SBI, RBL Bank.<ref>http://www.delhimetrorail.com/ATM_details.aspx</ref>\n\n==Entry/Exit==\n\nGate Number 1 - Metro Parking\n\nGate Number 2 - 3Cs Cinema\n\nGate Number 3 -  Defence Colony\n\n==Nearby==\nDefence Colony, Acharya  Munir Ashram, Rajkumari Amrit Kaur College of Nursing, Haldiram, The Japan Foundation, Guru Nanak Market, [[Ziyyara Edutech Private Limited]]\n\n==Connections==\n===Bus===\n[[Delhi Transport Corporation]] bus routes number 374, 404, 419, 419LSTL, 423, 425, 425CL, 425STL, 445, 445A, 445STL, 449CL, 490, 521, 727 serves the station.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://delhi.gov.in/wps/wcm/connect/DOIT_DTC/dtc/home |title=Archived copy |access-date=15 February 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181025080536/http://delhi.gov.in/wps/wcm/connect/doit_dtc/DTC/Home/ |archive-date=25 October 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n===Rail===\n[[Lajpat Nagar railway station]] of [[Delhi Suburban Railway]] is situated at 1.5&nbsp;km on Sardar Inderjit Singh Bhatia Rd.\n