{"title_page": "1893 Georgetown football team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox college sports team season\n| sport = football\n| year = 1893\n| team = Georgetown\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| conference = Independent\n| record = 4\u20134\n| head_coach = [[Dick Harley]]\n| hc_year = 1st\n| off_scheme = \n| def_scheme = \n| captain = \n| stadium = [[Boundary Field]]\n}}\n{{1893 Southern college football independents records}}\nThe '''1893 Georgetown Hoyas football team''' represented the [[Georgetown University]] during the [[1893 college football season]].  Georgetown finished the season with a 4\u20134 record.  [[Dick Harley]] served as player-coach.  They played home games at [[Boundary Park]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hoyafootball.com/records/games-1890s.htm|publisher=Hoya Football Project|title=Game By Game: 1891-1900|accessdate=March 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hoyasaxa.com/sports/hist01.htm|publisher=Hoya Saxa|title=Georgetown Football History: Chapter 1, Football's Roots at Georgetown|accessdate=March 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Schedule==\n{{CFB schedule\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 10\n| time = \n| w/l = l\n| opponent = [[1893 Penn Quakers football team|Penn]]\n| stadium = [[Boundary Field]]\n| cityst = [[Washington, D.C.|Washington, DC]]\n| score = 0\u201312\n| attend = \n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 14\n| time = \n| w/l = w\n| opponent = Washington YMCA\n| stadium = Boundary Field\n| cityst = Washington, DC\n| score = 16\u20130\n| attend = \n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 21\n| time = \n| w/l = w\n| opponent = {{cfb link|year=1893|team=Swarthmore Garnet Tide|title=Swarthmore}}\n| stadium = Boundary Field\n| cityst = Washington, DC\n| score = 34\u201310\n| attend = 7,000\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 25\n| time = \n| w/l = w\n| opponent = Washington YMCA\n| stadium = Boundary Field\n| cityst = Washington, DC\n| score = 10\u20138\n| at